The monsters: 3:34 Spriggans shoot poison lasers and usually spawn whenever a crop is destroyed. 4:15 Krakes move very fast, but they only attack if you hurt them or if you sprint near them. 5:06 Nymphs occasionally heal you if you're nearby. 7:37 Reapers attack sleeping players and inflict a custom Fear effect that messes up your movement. 9:28 Jengus spawn in water and attack any player nearby by firing water-spawning projectiles.  - They drop these projectiles on death, which is why Jschlatt was able to throw them at Tommy & Charlie in 10:15. 14:35 Striders (no, not the nether kind) spawn in water and attack players by picking them up and dealing constant damage. 14:48 Rocs just... pick players up whenever they feel like it. 22:49 Geists appear whenever an undead creature dies and inflict several debuffs on nearby players. When killed, they leave behind purple fire that causes the Wither effect. 23:17 Chupacabras spawn in caves and heal whenever they attack another creature. 23:23 Gnekks are devil-like creatures that inflict the Poison effect. 25:35 Ventoraptors are fast-moving bird creatures that can be tamed as mounts.  Those are all the mobs I've seen from the _Lycanite's Mobs_ mod of the RL Craft modpack.

When the last slice of pizza is gone 16:57
Ok here's a little post that I hope can help you guys! I don't even know if you'll SEE IT but I've been playing rlcraft for fun for a bit and thought you might enjoy a few quick tips here! Please like this so tommy might have a CHANCE of seeing it!  This is just beginner stuff, if you want a late game one later I'd love to make one for you guys!   Biggest things and how to deal with them:  Dragons!  HOW TO DEAL WITH THEM: Dragons stick in a certain proximity to their nest. Fire dragon nests have gold in them, and Ice dragons have silver. If you go underground and find a dragon nest, be warned! That is a level five! level five dragons are the one dragon type that will NOT stay by their nests once they are woken up! Level five dragons are the only ones that have a chance of dropping DRAGON EGGS! You can raise them, but I would suggest saving that for late game! BASICALLY! Do not go near nests unless you can speed the fuck out of there. They will be alerted if you break their gold, so I'd just avoid them until late game.   SEASONS!  NEED TO KNOW: Seasons aren't exactly something you beat, because they're going to beat you. Once winter comes, you're kinda f*cked if you don't have a way of keeping yourself warm! The easiest way is to wear wool armor and sit next to a campfire for a while. Otherwise, in mid-late winter, you will freeze to death every time you go outside. (I would suggest making a season clock to help tell what season it is) CROPS! Certain crops are only able to be grown in certain seasons! The crops and their various seasons are as follows:  SPRING: Carrots and Potatoes  SUMMER: Melon, Sugarcane, and Wheat  AUTUMN: Beetroot, Carrot, Pumpkin, and Wheat.  Saplings, flowers, and ferns grow in every season  MOST HELPFUL THINGS TO HAVE/KNOW ABOUT IN RLCRAFT:  SUMMONING STAFF! Bone, gold, eye of ender! thats all you need for a summoning staff! One of the most OP weapons in rlcraft. It can be used to summon mobs to fight for you! Press B to go into the menu, it's all very straightforward. I HIGHLY suggest getting one of these and leveling up your magic to use it.  Backpacks! there is a mod installed that gives you a backpack! You can put items in it, though it does replace your chest plate. When you die, your items will not despawn if they have been put inside the backpack. Its a very helpful item to have as you can craft them and carry them with you anywhere, as well as being able to place them and use them as chests!  Healing items! Bandages and shit are pretty useful if you're just going on a quick expedition, or on a perilous trip into the mines! Certain healing items can be held and just used on different body parts, or just held and used to heal overall body health. Keep your head on your shoulders, bois! If your head gets hit three times, your entire body is down for the count!  WEAPONS! There is a mod installed that gives you different weapons with different uses, I would say the best one is the halberd, as it does ASSLOADS of damage and has good reach! Also, if you use a two handed weapon with a shield, your attack speed will be very much so impaired! (u fight slow)  COMPANIONS VERY IMPORTANT!  When I say companions I mean pets and mounts that you can have! I saw you guys lose fuckworld, and I thought you might want to know about this stuff if you keep any more pets.  SOULSTONES! A soulstone is made by using a soulgazer, four eyes of ender, and four diamonds. A soulgazer can be used more than once to make more soulstones, but a soulstone can only be used ONCE on a tamed mob! I am telling you how to make a stone before how to tame, because in RLCRAFT it's foolish to go and tame a creature without having a soulstone to bind it! The reason being, once a creature is bound it can be revived/ summoned even after it dies over and over- after a cool down of about two minutes, of course. Soulstones can be used on pets and mountable creatures!  TAMING: You must make different treats depending on what you are trying to tame! The best mounts in the game are the morock and the roc, as they are tamable FLYING creatures and make travel a lot easier! As well as making it so you can fight large creatures from long range, and shoot battletower golems RIGHT OFF THEIR TOWERS! Rocs are the easiest and most common. You just need avian treats and a saddle! (SADDLES CAN BE CRAFTED). Once you have tamed it, use your soulstone and boom! Eternal companion!! You can also put chests on them and use them as storage that you can summon at will!   The best armor in the game is seaserpent armor, by the by. Seaserpents are vicious beasts, though! So be wary!   Battletowers are the best way to get loot quickly, so if you defeat the golem up top everything will breakdown.   NETHER IS NOT WORTH IT IN MY OPINION. JUST DEATH THERE.   final quick tips!  Enchant, enchant, enchant!  Dynamic trees can break your fall if you jump on to them!  JEI (just enough items) can tell you how to craft anything you could possibly want!    I hope this helps y'all! If you even see it!   Have a great day, and don't let rlcraft beat ya down! YOU GOT THIS!

Biggest things and how to deal with them:  Dragons!  HOW TO DEAL WITH THEM: Dragons stick in a certain proximity to their nest. Fire dragon nests have gold in them, and Ice dragons have silver. If you go underground and find a dragon nest, be warned! That is a level five! level five dragons are the one dragon type that will NOT stay by their nests once they are woken up! Level five dragons are the only ones that have a chance of dropping DRAGON EGGS! You can raise them, but I would suggest saving that for late game! BASICALLY! Do not go near nests unless you can speed the fuck out of there. They will be alerted if you break their gold, so I'd just avoid them until late game.   SEASONS!  NEED TO KNOW: Seasons aren't exactly something you beat, because they're going to beat you. Once winter comes, you're kinda f*cked if you don't have a way of keeping yourself warm! The easiest way is to wear wool armor and sit next to a campfire for a while. Otherwise, in mid-late winter, you will freeze to death every time you go outside. (I would suggest making a season clock to help tell what season it is) CROPS! Certain crops are only able to be grown in certain seasons! The crops and their various seasons are as follows:  SPRING: Carrots and Potatoes  SUMMER: Melon, Sugarcane, and Wheat  AUTUMN: Beetroot, Carrot, Pumpkin, and Wheat.  Saplings, flowers, and ferns grow in every season  MOST HELPFUL THINGS TO HAVE/KNOW ABOUT IN RLCRAFT:  SUMMONING STAFF! Bone, gold, eye of ender! thats all you need for a summoning staff! One of the most OP weapons in rlcraft. It can be used to summon mobs to fight for you! Press B to go into the menu, it's all very straightforward. I HIGHLY suggest getting one of these and leveling up your magic to use it.  Backpacks! there is a mod installed that gives you a backpack! You can put items in it, though it does replace your chest plate. When you die, your items will not despawn if they have been put inside the backpack. Its a very helpful item to have as you can craft them and carry them with you anywhere, as well as being able to place them and use them as chests!  Healing items! Bandages and shit are pretty useful if you're just going on a quick expedition, or on a perilous trip into the mines! Certain healing items can be held and just used on different body parts, or just held and used to heal overall body health. Keep your head on your shoulders, bois! If your head gets hit three times, your entire body is down for the count!  WEAPONS! There is a mod installed that gives you different weapons with different uses, I would say the best one is the halberd, as it does ASSLOADS of damage and has good reach! Also, if you use a two handed weapon with a shield, your attack speed will be very much so impaired! (u fight slow)  COMPANIONS VERY IMPORTANT!  When I say companions I mean pets and mounts that you can have! I saw you guys lose fuckworld, and I thought you might want to know about this stuff if you keep any more pets.  SOULSTONES! A soulstone is made by using a soulgazer, four eyes of ender, and four diamonds. A soulgazer can be used more than once to make more soulstones, but a soulstone can only be used ONCE on a tamed mob! I am telling you how to make a stone before how to tame, because in RLCRAFT it's foolish to go and tame a creature without having a soulstone to bind it! The reason being, once a creature is bound it can be revived/ summoned even after it dies over and over- after a cool down of about two minutes, of course. Soulstones can be used on pets and mountable creatures!  TAMING: You must make different treats depending on what you are trying to tame! The best mounts in the game are the morock and the roc, as they are tamable FLYING creatures and make travel a lot easier! As well as making it so you can fight large creatures from long range, and shoot battletower golems RIGHT OFF THEIR TOWERS! Rocs are the easiest and most common. You just need avian treats and a saddle! (SADDLES CAN BE CRAFTED). Once you have tamed it, use your soulstone and boom! Eternal companion!! You can also put chests on them and use them as storage that you can summon at will!   The best armor in the game is seaserpent armor, by the by. Seaserpents are vicious beasts, though! So be wary!   Battletowers are the best way to get loot quickly, so if you defeat the golem up top everything will breakdown.   NETHER IS NOT WORTH IT IN MY OPINION. JUST DEATH THERE.   final quick tips!  Enchant, enchant, enchant!  Dynamic trees can break your fall if you jump on to them!  JEI (just enough items) can tell you how to craft anything you could possibly want!    I hope this helps y'all! If you even see it!   Have a great day, and don't let rlcraft beat ya down! YOU GOT THIS!

Ok here's a little post that I hope can help you guys! I don't even know if you'll SEE IT but I've been playing rlcraft for fun for a bit and thought you might enjoy a few quick tips here! Please like this so tommy might have a CHANCE of seeing it!  This is just beginner stuff, if you want a late game one later I'd love to make one for you guys!   Biggest things and how to deal with them:  Dragons!  HOW TO DEAL WITH THEM: Dragons stick in a certain proximity to their nest. Fire dragon nests have gold in them, and Ice dragons have silver. If you go underground and find a dragon nest, be warned! That is a level five! level five dragons are the one dragon type that will NOT stay by their nests once they are woken up! Level five dragons are the only ones that have a chance of dropping DRAGON EGGS! You can raise them, but I would suggest saving that for late game! BASICALLY! Do not go near nests unless you can speed the fuck out of there. They will be alerted if you break their gold, so I'd just avoid them until late game.   SEASONS!  NEED TO KNOW: Seasons aren't exactly something you beat, because they're going to beat you. Once winter comes, you're kinda f*cked if you don't have a way of keeping yourself warm! The easiest way is to wear wool armor and sit next to a campfire for a while. Otherwise, in mid-late winter, you will freeze to death every time you go outside. (I would suggest making a season clock to help tell what season it is) CROPS! Certain crops are only able to be grown in certain seasons! The crops and their various seasons are as follows:  SPRING: Carrots and Potatoes  SUMMER: Melon, Sugarcane, and Wheat  AUTUMN: Beetroot, Carrot, Pumpkin, and Wheat.  Saplings, flowers, and ferns grow in every season  MOST HELPFUL THINGS TO HAVE/KNOW ABOUT IN RLCRAFT:  SUMMONING STAFF! Bone, gold, eye of ender! thats all you need for a summoning staff! One of the most OP weapons in rlcraft. It can be used to summon mobs to fight for you! Press B to go into the menu, it's all very straightforward. I HIGHLY suggest getting one of these and leveling up your magic to use it.  Backpacks! there is a mod installed that gives you a backpack! You can put items in it, though it does replace your chest plate. When you die, your items will not despawn if they have been put inside the backpack. Its a very helpful item to have as you can craft them and carry them with you anywhere, as well as being able to place them and use them as chests!  Healing items! Bandages and shit are pretty useful if you're just going on a quick expedition, or on a perilous trip into the mines! Certain healing items can be held and just used on different body parts, or just held and used to heal overall body health. Keep your head on your shoulders, bois! If your head gets hit three times, your entire body is down for the count!  WEAPONS! There is a mod installed that gives you different weapons with different uses, I would say the best one is the halberd, as it does ASSLOADS of damage and has good reach! Also, if you use a two handed weapon with a shield, your attack speed will be very much so impaired! (u fight slow)  COMPANIONS VERY IMPORTANT!  When I say companions I mean pets and mounts that you can have! I saw you guys lose fuckworld, and I thought you might want to know about this stuff if you keep any more pets.  SOULSTONES! A soulstone is made by using a soulgazer, four eyes of ender, and four diamonds. A soulgazer can be used more than once to make more soulstones, but a soulstone can only be used ONCE on a tamed mob! I am telling you how to make a stone before how to tame, because in RLCRAFT it's foolish to go and tame a creature without having a soulstone to bind it! The reason being, once a creature is bound it can be revived/ summoned even after it dies over and over- after a cool down of about two minutes, of course. Soulstones can be used on pets and mountable creatures!  TAMING: You must make different treats depending on what you are trying to tame! The best mounts in the game are the morock and the roc, as they are tamable FLYING creatures and make travel a lot easier! As well as making it so you can fight large creatures from long range, and shoot battletower golems RIGHT OFF THEIR TOWERS! Rocs are the easiest and most common. You just need avian treats and a saddle! (SADDLES CAN BE CRAFTED). Once you have tamed it, use your soulstone and boom! Eternal companion!! You can also put chests on them and use them as storage that you can summon at will!   The best armor in the game is seaserpent armor, by the by. Seaserpents are vicious beasts, though! So be wary!   Battletowers are the best way to get loot quickly, so if you defeat the golem up top everything will breakdown.   NETHER IS NOT WORTH IT IN MY OPINION. JUST DEATH THERE.   final quick tips!  Enchant, enchant, enchant!  Dynamic trees can break your fall if you jump on to them!  JEI (just enough items) can tell you how to craft anything you could possibly want!    I hope this helps y'all! If you even see it!   Have a great day, and don't let rlcraft beat ya down! YOU GOT THIS!

Ok here's a little post that I hope can help you guys! I don't even know if you'll SEE IT but I've been playing rlcraft for fun for a bit and thought you might enjoy a few quick tips here! Please like this so tommy might have a CHANCE of seeing it!  This is just beginner stuff, if you want a late game one later I'd love to make one for you guys!   Biggest things and how to deal with them:  Dragons!  HOW TO DEAL WITH THEM: Dragons stick in a certain proximity to their nest. Fire dragon nests have gold in them, and Ice dragons have silver. If you go underground and find a dragon nest, be warned! That is a level five! level five dragons are the one dragon type that will NOT stay by their nests once they are woken up! Level five dragons are the only ones that have a chance of dropping DRAGON EGGS! You can raise them, but I would suggest saving that for late game! BASICALLY! Do not go near nests unless you can speed the fuck out of there. They will be alerted if you break their gold, so I'd just avoid them until late game.   SEASONS!  NEED TO KNOW: Seasons aren't exactly something you beat, because they're going to beat you. Once winter comes, you're kinda f*cked if you don't have a way of keeping yourself warm! The easiest way is to wear wool armor and sit next to a campfire for a while. Otherwise, in mid-late winter, you will freeze to death every time you go outside. (I would suggest making a season clock to help tell what season it is) CROPS! Certain crops are only able to be grown in certain seasons! The crops and their various seasons are as follows:  SPRING: Carrots and Potatoes  SUMMER: Melon, Sugarcane, and Wheat  AUTUMN: Beetroot, Carrot, Pumpkin, and Wheat.  Saplings, flowers, and ferns grow in every season  MOST HELPFUL THINGS TO HAVE/KNOW ABOUT IN RLCRAFT:  SUMMONING STAFF! Bone, gold, eye of ender! thats all you need for a summoning staff! One of the most OP weapons in rlcraft. It can be used to summon mobs to fight for you! Press B to go into the menu, it's all very straightforward. I HIGHLY suggest getting one of these and leveling up your magic to use it.  Backpacks! there is a mod installed that gives you a backpack! You can put items in it, though it does replace your chest plate. When you die, your items will not despawn if they have been put inside the backpack. Its a very helpful item to have as you can craft them and carry them with you anywhere, as well as being able to place them and use them as chests!  Healing items! Bandages and shit are pretty useful if you're just going on a quick expedition, or on a perilous trip into the mines! Certain healing items can be held and just used on different body parts, or just held and used to heal overall body health. Keep your head on your shoulders, bois! If your head gets hit three times, your entire body is down for the count!  WEAPONS! There is a mod installed that gives you different weapons with different uses, I would say the best one is the halberd, as it does ASSLOADS of damage and has good reach! Also, if you use a two handed weapon with a shield, your attack speed will be very much so impaired! (u fight slow)  COMPANIONS VERY IMPORTANT!  When I say companions I mean pets and mounts that you can have! I saw you guys lose fuckworld, and I thought you might want to know about this stuff if you keep any more pets.  SOULSTONES! A soulstone is made by using a soulgazer, four eyes of ender, and four diamonds. A soulgazer can be used more than once to make more soulstones, but a soulstone can only be used ONCE on a tamed mob! I am telling you how to make a stone before how to tame, because in RLCRAFT it's foolish to go and tame a creature without having a soulstone to bind it! The reason being, once a creature is bound it can be revived/ summoned even after it dies over and over- after a cool down of about two minutes, of course. Soulstones can be used on pets and mountable creatures!  TAMING: You must make different treats depending on what you are trying to tame! The best mounts in the game are the morock and the roc, as they are tamable FLYING creatures and make travel a lot easier! As well as making it so you can fight large creatures from long range, and shoot battletower golems RIGHT OFF THEIR TOWERS! Rocs are the easiest and most common. You just need avian treats and a saddle! (SADDLES CAN BE CRAFTED). Once you have tamed it, use your soulstone and boom! Eternal companion!! You can also put chests on them and use them as storage that you can summon at will!   The best armor in the game is seaserpent armor, by the by. Seaserpents are vicious beasts, though! So be wary!   Battletowers are the best way to get loot quickly, so if you defeat the golem up top everything will breakdown.   NETHER IS NOT WORTH IT IN MY OPINION. JUST DEATH THERE.   final quick tips!  Enchant, enchant, enchant!  Dynamic trees can break your fall if you jump on to them!  JEI (just enough items) can tell you how to craft anything you could possibly want!    I hope this helps y'all! If you even see it!   Have a great day, and don't let rlcraft beat ya down! YOU GOT THIS!

When you're a 10 year old, one year is 10% of your entire life. When your 60 years old, one year is 1.7% of your entire life. Human beings are all about perspective, and this is why everything is so dramatic for the youth, and why older people generally handle things more calmly. I call it my percentage/perspective theory.  It's easy to tell a child not to take something so seriously from your older perspective, but you shouldn't forget their younger perspective. If you graduate high school at the age of 18, the last 4 years have been 22% of your entire life. If you graduate high school at the age of 18 you will have spent 67% of your life in school. If you graduate with a bachelor's degree at the age of 22, the last 4 years will have been 18% of your entire life, and you will have spent 73% of your entire life  on education.  If you live to be 70 years old and you look back on your education it will seem as if time flew, as the 16 years you spent getting educated is now only 23% of your entire life.  Life is all about perspective, because perspective is the individuality of man. If you use my percentage/perspective theory you can make a lot of sense of the illusion of time.

this looks like the most intense thing i have seen
It's not the hardest modpack, that would be the RotN modpack.   RLCraft was originally meant as a joke and is more akin to a lottery than any actual difficulty : you either die instantly because you spawned in a bad spot or survive because you ended up in a good one, and even then luck plays a heavy role in it because if you mine one wrong block or kill one too many animal, some random mob spawns that'll instantly kill you if you don't have enough gear or health - gear that you have to obtain by mining and health that can only gain back by eating. It's a bad design.  Not only that, but even once you have good gear and a somewhat secure home, you still have to grind for ages just to be able to use better swords or armor, or farma certain source of food, or use a certain tool, and the game quickly becomes repetitive and boring because of that random arbitrary limitation that is there just because the guy who made the modpack couldn't be bothered to remove some structures to stop you from getting OP gear instantly.  To be honest, it's sad to know RLCraft is such a popular modpack, and that it has become many people's introduction to modding : it's on the front page of curse forge ffs! There's so many good mods in this modpack that just don't work well with the other mods of the pack and create this huge incoherent mess of designs, items, mobs and blocks.

attempt THREE!  Ok here's a little post that I hope can help you guys! I don't even know if you'll SEE IT but I've been playing rlcraft for fun for a bit and thought you might enjoy a few quick tips here! Please like this so tommy might have a CHANCE of seeing it!  This is just beginner stuff, if you want a late game one later I'd love to make one for you guys!   Biggest things and how to deal with them:  Dragons!  HOW TO DEAL WITH THEM: Dragons stick in a certain proximity to their nest. Fire dragon nests have gold in them, and Ice dragons have silver. If you go underground and find a dragon nest, be warned! That is a level five! level five dragons are the one dragon type that will NOT stay by their nests once they are woken up! Level five dragons are the only ones that have a chance of dropping DRAGON EGGS! You can raise them, but I would suggest saving that for late game! BASICALLY! Do not go near nests unless you can speed the fuck out of there. They will be alerted if you break their gold, so I'd just avoid them until late game.   SEASONS!  NEED TO KNOW: Seasons aren't exactly something you beat, because they're going to beat you. Once winter comes, you're kinda f*cked if you don't have a way of keeping yourself warm! The easiest way is to wear wool armor and sit next to a campfire for a while. Otherwise, in mid-late winter, you will freeze to death every time you go outside. (I would suggest making a season clock to help tell what season it is) CROPS! Certain crops are only able to be grown in certain seasons! The crops and their various seasons are as follows:  SPRING: Carrots and Potatoes  SUMMER: Melon, Sugarcane, and Wheat  AUTUMN: Beetroot, Carrot, Pumpkin, and Wheat.  Saplings, flowers, and ferns grow in every season  MOST HELPFUL THINGS TO HAVE/KNOW ABOUT IN RLCRAFT:  SUMMONING STAFF! Bone, gold, eye of ender! thats all you need for a summoning staff! One of the most OP weapons in rlcraft. It can be used to summon mobs to fight for you! Press B to go into the menu, it's all very straightforward. I HIGHLY suggest getting one of these and leveling up your magic to use it.  Backpacks! there is a mod installed that gives you a backpack! You can put items in it, though it does replace your chest plate. When you die, your items will not despawn if they have been put inside the backpack. Its a very helpful item to have as you can craft them and carry them with you anywhere, as well as being able to place them and use them as chests!  Healing items! Bandages and shit are pretty useful if you're just going on a quick expedition, or on a perilous trip into the mines! Certain healing items can be held and just used on different body parts, or just held and used to heal overall body health. Keep your head on your shoulders, bois! If your head gets hit three times, your entire body is down for the count!  WEAPONS! There is a mod installed that gives you different weapons with different uses, I would say the best one is the halberd, as it does ASSLOADS of damage and has good reach! Also, if you use a two handed weapon with a shield, your attack speed will be very much so impaired! (u fight slow)  COMPANIONS VERY IMPORTANT!  When I say companions I mean pets and mounts that you can have! I saw you guys lose fuckworld, and I thought you might want to know about this stuff if you keep any more pets.  SOULSTONES! A soulstone is made by using a soulgazer, four eyes of ender, and four diamonds. A soulgazer can be used more than once to make more soulstones, but a soulstone can only be used ONCE on a tamed mob! I am telling you how to make a stone before how to tame, because in RLCRAFT it's foolish to go and tame a creature without having a soulstone to bind it! The reason being, once a creature is bound it can be revived/ summoned even after it dies over and over- after a cool down of about two minutes, of course. Soulstones can be used on pets and mountable creatures!  TAMING: You must make different treats depending on what you are trying to tame! The best mounts in the game are the morock and the roc, as they are tamable FLYING creatures and make travel a lot easier! As well as making it so you can fight large creatures from long range, and shoot battletower golems RIGHT OFF THEIR TOWERS! Rocs are the easiest and most common. You just need avian treats and a saddle! (SADDLES CAN BE CRAFTED). Once you have tamed it, use your soulstone and boom! Eternal companion!! You can also put chests on them and use them as storage that you can summon at will!   The best armor in the game is seaserpent armor, by the by. Seaserpents are vicious beasts, though! So be wary!   Battletowers are the best way to get loot quickly, so if you defeat the golem up top everything will breakdown.   NETHER IS NOT WORTH IT IN MY OPINION. JUST DEATH THERE.   final quick tips!  Enchant, enchant, enchant!  Dynamic trees can break your fall if you jump on to them!  JEI (just enough items) can tell you how to craft anything you could possibly want!    I hope this helps y'all! If you even see it!   Have a great day, and don't let rlcraft beat ya down! YOU GOT THIS!

attempt two!  Ok here's a little post that I hope can help you guys! I don't even know if you'll SEE IT but I've been playing rlcraft for fun for a bit and thought you might enjoy a few quick tips here! Please like this so tommy might have a CHANCE of seeing it!  This is just beginner stuff, if you want a late game one later I'd love to make one for you guys!   Biggest things and how to deal with them:  Dragons!  HOW TO DEAL WITH THEM: Dragons stick in a certain proximity to their nest. Fire dragon nests have gold in them, and Ice dragons have silver. If you go underground and find a dragon nest, be warned! That is a level five! level five dragons are the one dragon type that will NOT stay by their nests once they are woken up! Level five dragons are the only ones that have a chance of dropping DRAGON EGGS! You can raise them, but I would suggest saving that for late game! BASICALLY! Do not go near nests unless you can speed the fuck out of there. They will be alerted if you break their gold, so I'd just avoid them until late game.   SEASONS!  NEED TO KNOW: Seasons aren't exactly something you beat, because they're going to beat you. Once winter comes, you're kinda f*cked if you don't have a way of keeping yourself warm! The easiest way is to wear wool armor and sit next to a campfire for a while. Otherwise, in mid-late winter, you will freeze to death every time you go outside. (I would suggest making a season clock to help tell what season it is) CROPS! Certain crops are only able to be grown in certain seasons! The crops and their various seasons are as follows:  SPRING: Carrots and Potatoes  SUMMER: Melon, Sugarcane, and Wheat  AUTUMN: Beetroot, Carrot, Pumpkin, and Wheat.  Saplings, flowers, and ferns grow in every season  MOST HELPFUL THINGS TO HAVE/KNOW ABOUT IN RLCRAFT:  SUMMONING STAFF! Bone, gold, eye of ender! thats all you need for a summoning staff! One of the most OP weapons in rlcraft. It can be used to summon mobs to fight for you! Press B to go into the menu, it's all very straightforward. I HIGHLY suggest getting one of these and leveling up your magic to use it.  Backpacks! there is a mod installed that gives you a backpack! You can put items in it, though it does replace your chest plate. When you die, your items will not despawn if they have been put inside the backpack. Its a very helpful item to have as you can craft them and carry them with you anywhere, as well as being able to place them and use them as chests!  Healing items! Bandages and shit are pretty useful if you're just going on a quick expedition, or on a perilous trip into the mines! Certain healing items can be held and just used on different body parts, or just held and used to heal overall body health. Keep your head on your shoulders, bois! If your head gets hit three times, your entire body is down for the count!  WEAPONS! There is a mod installed that gives you different weapons with different uses, I would say the best one is the halberd, as it does ASSLOADS of damage and has good reach! Also, if you use a two handed weapon with a shield, your attack speed will be very much so impaired! (u fight slow)  COMPANIONS VERY IMPORTANT!  When I say companions I mean pets and mounts that you can have! I saw you guys lose fuckworld, and I thought you might want to know about this stuff if you keep any more pets.  SOULSTONES! A soulstone is made by using a soulgazer, four eyes of ender, and four diamonds. A soulgazer can be used more than once to make more soulstones, but a soulstone can only be used ONCE on a tamed mob! I am telling you how to make a stone before how to tame, because in RLCRAFT it's foolish to go and tame a creature without having a soulstone to bind it! The reason being, once a creature is bound it can be revived/ summoned even after it dies over and over- after a cool down of about two minutes, of course. Soulstones can be used on pets and mountable creatures!  TAMING: You must make different treats depending on what you are trying to tame! The best mounts in the game are the morock and the roc, as they are tamable FLYING creatures and make travel a lot easier! As well as making it so you can fight large creatures from long range, and shoot battletower golems RIGHT OFF THEIR TOWERS! Rocs are the easiest and most common. You just need avian treats and a saddle! (SADDLES CAN BE CRAFTED). Once you have tamed it, use your soulstone and boom! Eternal companion!! You can also put chests on them and use them as storage that you can summon at will!   The best armor in the game is seaserpent armor, by the by. Seaserpents are vicious beasts, though! So be wary!   Battletowers are the best way to get loot quickly, so if you defeat the golem up top everything will breakdown.   NETHER IS NOT WORTH IT IN MY OPINION. JUST DEATH THERE.   final quick tips!  Enchant, enchant, enchant!  Dynamic trees can break your fall if you jump on to them!  JEI (just enough items) can tell you how to craft anything you could possibly want!    I hope this helps y'all! If you even see it!   Have a great day, and don't let rlcraft beat ya down! YOU GOT THIS!

Hi
Hey Tommy can you survive 200 days in RLcraft?
Ok here's a little post that I hope can help you guys! I don't even know if you'll SEE IT but I've been playing rlcraft for fun for a bit and thought you might enjoy a few quick tips here! Please like this so tommy might have a CHANCE of seeing it!  This is just beginner stuff, if you want a late game one later I'd love to make one for you guys!   Biggest things and how to deal with them:  Dragons!  HOW TO DEAL WITH THEM: Dragons stick in a certain proximity to their nest. Fire dragon nests have gold in them, and Ice dragons have silver. If you go underground and find a dragon nest, be warned! That is a level five! level five dragons are the one dragon type that will NOT stay by their nests once they are woken up! Level five dragons are the only ones that have a chance of dropping DRAGON EGGS! You can raise them, but I would suggest saving that for late game! BASICALLY! Do not go near nests unless you can speed the fuck out of there. They will be alerted if you break their gold, so I'd just avoid them until late game.   SEASONS!  NEED TO KNOW: Seasons aren't exactly something you beat, because they're going to beat you. Once winter comes, you're kinda f*cked if you don't have a way of keeping yourself warm! The easiest way is to wear wool armor and sit next to a campfire for a while. Otherwise, in mid-late winter, you will freeze to death every time you go outside. (I would suggest making a season clock to help tell what season it is) CROPS! Certain crops are only able to be grown in certain seasons! The crops and their various seasons are as follows:  SPRING: Carrots and Potatoes  SUMMER: Melon, Sugarcane, and Wheat  AUTUMN: Beetroot, Carrot, Pumpkin, and Wheat.  Saplings, flowers, and ferns grow in every season  MOST HELPFUL THINGS TO HAVE/KNOW ABOUT IN RLCRAFT:  SUMMONING STAFF! Bone, gold, eye of ender! thats all you need for a summoning staff! One of the most OP weapons in rlcraft. It can be used to summon mobs to fight for you! Press B to go into the menu, it's all very straightforward. I HIGHLY suggest getting one of these and leveling up your magic to use it.  Backpacks! there is a mod installed that gives you a backpack! You can put items in it, though it does replace your chest plate. When you die, your items will not despawn if they have been put inside the backpack. Its a very helpful item to have as you can craft them and carry them with you anywhere, as well as being able to place them and use them as chests!  Healing items! Bandages and shit are pretty useful if you're just going on a quick expedition, or on a perilous trip into the mines! Certain healing items can be held and just used on different body parts, or just held and used to heal overall body health. Keep your head on your shoulders, bois! If your head gets hit three times, your entire body is down for the count!  WEAPONS! There is a mod installed that gives you different weapons with different uses, I would say the best one is the halberd, as it does ASSLOADS of damage and has good reach! Also, if you use a two handed weapon with a shield, your attack speed will be very much so impaired! (u fight slow)  COMPANIONS *VERY IMPORTANT!*  When I say companions I mean pets and mounts that you can have! I saw you guys lose fuckworld, and I thought you might want to know about this stuff if you keep any more pets.  SOULSTONES! A soulstone is made by using a soulgazer, four eyes of ender, and four diamonds. A soulgazer can be used more than once to make more soulstones, but a soulstone can only be used ONCE on a tamed mob! I am telling you how to make a stone before how to tame, because in RLCRAFT it's foolish to go and tame a creature without having a soulstone to bind it! The reason being, once a creature is bound it can be revived/ summoned even after it dies over and over- after a cool down of about two minutes, of course. Soulstones can be used on pets and mountable creatures!  TAMING: You must make different treats depending on what you are trying to tame! The best mounts in the game are the morock and the roc, as they are tamable FLYING creatures and make travel a lot easier! As well as making it so you can fight large creatures from long range, and shoot battletower golems RIGHT OFF THEIR TOWERS! Rocs are the easiest and most common. You just need avian treats and a saddle! (SADDLES CAN BE CRAFTED). Once you have tamed it, use your soulstone and boom! Eternal companion!! You can also put chests on them and use them as storage that you can summon at will!   The best armor in the game is seaserpent armor, by the by. Seaserpents are vicious beasts, though! So be wary!   Battletowers are the best way to get loot quickly, so if you defeat the golem up top everything will breakdown.   NETHER IS NOT WORTH IT IN MY OPINION. JUST DEATH THERE.   final quick tips!  Enchant, enchant, enchant!  Dynamic trees can break your fall if you jump on to them!  JEI (just enough items) can tell you how to craft anything you could possibly want!    I hope this helps y'all! If you even see it!   Have a great day, and don't let rlcraft beat ya down! YOU GOT THIS!
